// const http = require('http')
import http from 'http'
import app from './app'
import connectDB from './config/database'
const server = http.createServer(app)

const port = 8000

server.listen(port, () => console.log(`Server is started and run on ${port}`))
connectDB()

import express from 'express'
import { register, login, getUser } from '../controllers/auth.controller'
const router = express.Router()

router.get("/", getUser)

router.post("/register", register)

router.post("/login", login)

module.exports = router

const devConfig = {
    jwt_key: "example_secret_key",
    jwt_expiration: 28800,
    dbConnectionString: `mongodb://localhost:27017/test_db`,
    mongoDebug: true
}

export default devConfig
